load\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-214_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"6e3fbad8-702f-4987-ad70-cc88122eea43","comments":[],"created_at":1784416831364056001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[{"link_uuid":"06d4ba09-4af4-462a-84a1-481c39882baa","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"0b96-cbcb-0ea2-479d"},{"link_uuid":"9250ec8f-803d-4970-95ea-d36fa28445dc","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"555e-3efa-4ad6-4169"}],"description":"## What\nOne-time backfill: run the conservative blame -> commit -> ticket resolver over existing closed bugs to draw `caused_by` links retroactively, seeding source-of-bugs history.\n\n## Files\n- `scripts/backfill_caused_by.py` — new: iterate closed bugs, reuse `src/rebar/metrics/blame.py`, draw `caused_by` on high-confidence single culprits; `--dry-run` default.\n- `tests/scripts/test_backfill_caused_by.py` — new.\n\n## Test tier\nThe test lives under `tests/scripts/` with `pytestmark = pytest.mark.scripts` (the scripts tier; `tests/unit/scripts/` does NOT exist). External tools are stubbed/mocked so the test is deterministic and needs no scc/lizard/jscpd installed.\n\n## Approach\nReuse the same conservative single-culprit resolver as the live auto-derivation (no new heuristic) so backfilled links are deterministic and consistent with going-forward ones. Idempotent via an EXPLICIT existing-link check: because the low-level `rebar.graph._links._write_link_event` writer has NO built-in idempotency (a closed-bug backfill must write via it, bypassing `add_dependency`'s closed-source guard), the script guards the write itself — before writing it calls `rebar.graph._links._is_active_link(bug_id, culprit_id, \"caused_by\", tracker_dir)` and SKIPS the bug when an active `caused_by` edge to that culprit already exists. `--dry-run` by default so a run previews before writing; back-out is removing the additive links.\n\n## Tests\n- Unit (temp store + git): over a fixture of two closed bugs (one single-culprit, one ambiguous), the script proposes exactly one `caused_by` link; a second run is a no-op.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `tests/scripts/test_backfill_caused_by.py` passes: the script links the single-culprit bug and skips the ambiguous one (`assert links == 1`).\n- [ ] re-running is idempotent — the test runs the script in WRITE mode (`--write`, NOT dry-run) twice: the first pass draws the caused_by link, and the second pass draws 0 new links because the bug already carries an active `caused_by` to its culprit (the script checks `_is_active_link` before writing). (`--dry-run` is the DEFAULT for safety; the idempotency AC explicitly opts into write mode.)\n- [ ] the backfill actually executes end-to-end: the test invokes the script's entry point (write mode) over a fixture store of two closed bugs (one single-culprit, one ambiguous) and asserts exactly ONE caused_by link is drawn (to the single-culprit's resolved ticket) and the ambiguous bug gets none — proving the script runs the real resolver, not just that a helper exists.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"scripts/backfill_caused_by.py","reason":"backfill script"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["depends_on","0b96-cbcb-0ea2-479d"],["depends_on","555e-3efa-4ad6-4169"],["parent","86ac-086a-20ad-4327"]],"parent_id":"86ac-086a-20ad-4327","parent_status_uuid":"26bb1a37-2250-4343-9c71-3268d88e10ba","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":["metrics","backfill"],"ticket_id":"2f8e-0f7e-6fea-4825","ticket_type":"task","title":"Backfill caused_by links over existing closed bugs (blame)","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["926c87dd-5ece-4d69-a8ed-f4924344863e","229f8085-2503-4977-b6dd-4b9fe1ce3333","06d4ba09-4af4-462a-84a1-481c39882baa","9250ec8f-803d-4970-95ea-d36fa28445dc","ca83fdc2-a597-45ca-ba84-eac21c6d109e","f9f0c700-1354-4f3e-8ac5-e3ebcd5e55fd","9cfcb9e4-52b0-4233-82fd-360a62fa7d21","074fde34-1f4d-41c9-818e-b35bde9e9499","10ab40e3-d41c-49ab-8bbe-dc93177ab121","26bb1a37-2250-4343-9c71-3268d88e10ba","237c22f1-62ae-4a25-826d-cb22620a2466","b0f2334a-f3dc-4c54-a7eb-367507b1f514"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784455635201071509,"uuid":"c626c10d-7d5e-4705-a9e4-9b9ec89340a0"}